# Engram Local Memory

## 2026-06-01 — Copilot Critical hardening + Today Workbench spec (Codex)

User approved the Today Workbench + Advanced noise-reduction direction, then
provided a Copilot multi-expert review. Recorded the review in
`docs/reviews/2026-06-01-copilot-product-hardening-review.md` and handled the
two Critical items before product UI expansion:

- `TerminalLauncher` now builds one shell-safe command line by shell-quoting
  `cwd`, command, and args before AppleScript interpolation. It reuses
  `EngramCLIResumeCommand.shellEscaped`, and `EngramCLIResumeCommandTests`
  covers semicolons, `$()` command substitution, quotes, spaces, backslashes,
  and AppleScript escaping after shell quoting.
- TS MCP project migration mutators now force fail-closed behavior through
  `shouldFallbackToDirectForTool`: `project_move`, `project_archive`,
  `project_undo`, and `project_move_batch` require the Swift service pipeline
  even when `mcpStrictSingleWriter` is false. `save_insight` keeps the old
  fallback semantics unless strict mode is enabled.
- Network settings copy now reflects the new boundary: project migration tools
  always require the Swift service; the toggle only controls remaining MCP write
  fallbacks.
- `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-01-today-workbench-design.md` records the
  approved product direction: Today as the default workbench, Search as
  retrieval, Advanced as the home for low-level filters/diagnostics, and shared
  visible-message rules for transcript noise reduction.
- Continued into the top Important follow-ups:
  - TS MCP/API `project_move_batch` now accepts inline JSON in the legacy
    `yaml` field, matching Swift service/MCP/docs. YAML payloads are rejected on
    MCP/API paths; CLI `move-batch <yaml-file>` remains YAML-compatible.
  - TS `get_session`, TS HTTP transcript routes, and Swift WebUI now share the
    default transcript predicate: non-empty user/assistant only, excluding tool,
    system prompt, and agent communication content. Diagnostic/raw routes remain
    available for low-level inspection.
  - HTTP transcript pagination now returns the next raw adapter offset instead
    of a filtered visible count, so hidden messages no longer cause skipped or
    repeated visible pages.
  - `EngramServiceLauncher` stdout event parsing now buffers newline-delimited
    JSON events across pipe chunks and logs decode failures with the raw line.
  - HOME-mutating Swift service-core tests now use `ServiceCoreTestHomeScope`,
    a serialized process-global HOME guard that restores the original value even
    on failure.
  - `ServiceWriterGateTests.testCancelledQueuedWriteCommandDoesNotExecuteLater`
    now waits for the semaphore waiter count instead of sleeping.
  - `EmbeddingIndexer` now has a real `Database` + `SqliteVecStore` integration
    test with a deterministic embedding client, covering persisted model fields
    and restart skip.
  - `check-adapter-parity-fixtures` now regenerates fixtures to a temp tree and
    canonical-compares the committed corpus, normalizing volatile commit/node
    metadata only.
  - CI now runs adapter parity freshness and makes screenshot comparison fail
    when UI jobs produce no manifest or a true size mismatch. Diff images are
    written to `screenshots/diffs/`, matching the uploaded artifact path.

